{"name": "cubicweb-comment", "metadata": {"name": "cubicweb-comment", "version": "3.0.0", "classifiers": ["Environment :: Web Environment", "Framework :: CubicWeb", "Programming Language :: JavaScript", "Programming Language :: Python"], "home_page": "https://forge.extranet.logilab.fr/cubicweb/cubes/cubicweb-comment", "license": "LGPL", "documentation_url": null, "dependencies": ["cubicweb", "cubicweb-web"], "summary": "commenting system for the CubicWeb framework", "upload_time": 1690277656}, "documentation": ["# Summary\n\nThe `comment` cube provides threadable comments feature.\n\nIt is a CubicWeb component. CubicWeb is a semantic web application\nframework, see <http://www.cubicweb.org>\n\n# Install\n\nAuto-install from sources prefered with *pip/Distribute*:\n\n```\npip install cubicweb-comment\n```\n\nIf you have troubles, use *easy_install/setuptools* and eggs:\n\n```\neasy_install cubicweb-comment\n```\n\nYou can install the package manually from the uncompressed\n[tarball](http://www.cubicweb.org/project/cubicweb-comment):\n\n```\npython setup.py install # auto-install dependencies\n```\n\nIf you don't want the dependancies to be installed automaticly, you\ncan force the setup to use the standard library *distutils*:\n\n```\nNO_SETUPTOOLS=1 python setup.py install\n```\n\nMore details at <http://www.cubicweb.org/doc/en/admin/setup>\n\n# Usage\n\nThis cube creates a new entity type called `Comment` which could basically be\nread by every body but only added by application's users.\nIt also defines a relation `comments` which provides the ability to add a\n`Comment` which `comments` a `Comment`.\n\nTo use this cube, you want to add the relation `comments` on the entity type\nyou want to be able to comment. For instance, let's say your cube defines a\nschema for a blog. You want all the blog entries to be commentable.\nHere is how to define it in your schema:\n\n```python\nfrom yams.buildobjs import RelationDefinition\nclass comments(RelationDefinition):\n    subject = 'Comment'\n    object = 'BlogEntry'\n    cardinality = '1*'\n```\n\nOnce this relation is defined, you can post comments and view threadable\ncomments automatically on blog entry's primary view.\n\n# Documentation\n\nLook in the `doc/` subdirectory or read\n<http://www.cubicweb.org/doc/en/>\n"], "modules": [{"name": "cubicweb_comment", "documentation": ["cubicweb comment"], "functions": [], "variables": [], "classes": [], "exports": []}, {"name": "cubicweb_comment.schema", "documentation": [":organization: Logilab\n:copyright: 2003-2010 LOGILAB S.A. (Paris, FRANCE), all rights reserved.\n:contact: http://www.logilab.fr/ -- mailto:contact@logilab.fr"], "functions": [], "variables": [], "classes": [{"name": "cubicweb_comment.schema.Comment", "bases": ["EntityType"], "methods": [], "class_variables": [{"name": "cubicweb_comment.schema.Comment.content", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "cubicweb_comment.schema.Comment.comments", "type": null, "documentation": []}], "instance_variables": [], "inner_classes": [], "documentation": ["a comment is a reply about another entity"]}, {"name": "cubicweb_comment.schema.comments", "bases": ["RelationType"], "methods": [], "class_variables": [{"name": "cubicweb_comment.schema.comments.__permissions__", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "cubicweb_comment.schema.comments.inlined", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "cubicweb_comment.schema.comments.composite", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "cubicweb_comment.schema.comments.cardinality", "type": null, "documentation": []}], "instance_variables": [], "inner_classes": [], "documentation": []}], "exports": []}, {"name": "cubicweb_comment.__pkginfo__", "documentation": ["cubicweb-comment packaging information", "pylint: disable-msg=W0622"], "functions": [], "variables": [{"name": "cubicweb_comment.__pkginfo__.modname", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "cubicweb_comment.__pkginfo__.distname", "type": null, "documentation"